On 3/2/2018 at 4:18 PM, Lilienthal said:

What I don't understand are the roll-out prices. How are they calculated?

First take the cost of the Craft, then multiple by several factors.  Each factor os based off of things that make it harder to launch/prepare the rocket.  These include various things like having toxic fuel or being man rated or having cryogenic fuel.  Then multiply by a factor based on the level of the launching pad.

You will want to buy and upgrade several pads so that you can use the lowest pad level for the craft you are launching.

Craft rollout costs will also dramaticly be higher if you do not Tool components.

Use the Green button to see tooling, and in VAB show a list of untooled parts on teh craft.

Hi @westleyTwain!

If you want to install visual mods try the install guide from Real Solar System Visual Enhancements rather than CKAN. There are different working versions of Scatterer, EVE, Kopernicus, and Module Manager depending on your version of KSP. 

If you want a "pure"  version of RP-0 using CKAN, have a clean install of KSP 1.2.2 and just select Realistic Progression Zero from CKAN. Then you will be prompted for your choice of texture size, choose the size you want and press Continue. Then you'll return to the list of mods, from there you should press Apply Changes (green checkmark). This will bring you a list of mods that are dependencies of RP-0, click Apply. Then you will get a list of recommended mods, here you can choose what recommended mods you want to install, if you want a bare bones RP-0 (not really recommended, RP-0 will not be much fun without some of these mods), then only accept the required mods (Deselect all recommended mods), and press continue. This will install RP-0 with only the required mods.

Then you can test RP-0 and the required mods to see if they work.

If the mods work fine, then you can install other mods one by one to find out which mods will break your game.

Good luck!
